red depends on the defaults for the browser, and for some reason, what style sheets have been recently applied (I guess they overwrite some defaults).  So what might look good to me on my browser looks awful on yours.  Italics vary especially.  <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Underline</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> bold</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> seem relatively stable, I will try to limit myself to judicious use of those, and avoid italics.<br>
<br>
The second purpose of using styles was to try to provide a &quot;voice&quot; to my writing, like rising and falling intonation.  Text lacks the social cues that we take for granted when we talk in person, like intonation, body language, and facial expressions, and in their absence people tend to project emotional content into the writing which may not reflect the intent of the writer.  For example, messages often come across as being meaner than the author intended.  This is one reason &quot;flames&quot; are so common on forums.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Balanz...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Sigh...Balanz was my first main, a dwarven paladin on Prexus.  In order to attend a wedding of a real life friend on Povar, I created a Magician there, having been impressed with a magician named Teker Magikos.  Ancient Fellowship turned out to a wonderful guild, and after the server split, Xev proved to be much less crowded than Prexus, so I have not played Balanz in months.  I don't want to give up my EZBoard account, especially the total # of posts next to my name.<br>
