<br>
If pre-battle, rods should go to whatever buffer is lowest on mana, and buffers with surplus mana (including paladins -- paladins are awesome for healing mod-rodding buffers) heal them. If a cleric uses just one rod or two, they should let regrowth handle the healing. When I play my cleric alt, if I don't have anyone else to heal me, I can suck down 3000 hps worth of mod rods and then CH myself. True, many clerics are lazy and don't do that. So I yell at them till they become reasonably efficient (at least using a heal dot. But remedy? Jeeze.)<br>
<br>
If during battle, no AoEs, cleric should either just suck up the damage or let their backup healer (druid/surplus shaman) heal them. With AoE's things get a bit hairy to use mod rods during a fight, since its IMPERATIVE not to go below 40% life as a cleric.<br>
<br>
